WEBVTT

1
00:00:12.106 --> 00:00:13.784
The Klaustreich...

2
00:00:13.909 --> 00:00:18.727
I came in contact with

3
00:00:18.893 --> 00:00:21.688
was aggressive...

4
00:00:25.399 --> 00:00:27.319
Predatory...

5
00:00:27.485 --> 00:00:30.405
And...

6
00:00:34.575 --> 00:00:36.557
A real ass.

7
00:00:36.682 --> 00:00:38.455
I can't write that.

8
00:00:38.621 --> 00:00:40.645
What's the word?

9
00:00:40.770 --> 00:00:42.834
Mean?
No.

10
00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:46.630
Catty?
Big no.

11
00:00:46.796 --> 00:00:48.882
Got it.

12
00:00:49.048 --> 00:00:51.385
Sadistic.

13
00:00:51.551 --> 00:00:53.387
And treacherous.

14
00:00:56.469 --> 00:01:04.022
♪ ♪

15
00:01:34.607 --> 00:01:37.305
What time does that leave?

16
00:02:59.275 --> 00:03:01.223
Thank you for calling Raz bus line.

17
00:03:22.464 --> 00:03:26.998
♪ ♪

18
00:04:07.409 --> 00:04:10.125
<i>Wenn sie verstehen was ich sage.</i>

19
00:04:10.291 --> 00:04:14.625
<i>dann lassen sie mich mal wissen.</i>

20
00:04:14.750 --> 00:04:16.464
Yes. I understand.

21
00:04:16.630 --> 00:04:19.129
<i>Sehr gut.</i>

22
00:04:19.254 --> 00:04:21.265
One can't be too careful.

23
00:04:21.390 --> 00:04:23.400
entering the home
of a police captain.

24
00:04:23.525 --> 00:04:26.850
before introductions are made.
you know.

25
00:04:27.016 --> 00:04:30.187
So true.

26
00:04:30.353 --> 00:04:35.317
I was just. uh. following protocol.

27
00:04:35.483 --> 00:04:36.664
I don't care if you are
working for the Verrat.

28
00:04:36.789 --> 00:04:39.350
The next time you let yourself
into my home uninvited.

29
00:04:39.475 --> 00:04:41.865
I will shoot you.

30
00:04:42.031 --> 00:04:44.054
In self-defense. of course.

31
00:04:44.179 --> 00:04:45.823
My dear Captain.

32
00:04:45.948 --> 00:04:48.496
if you didn't speak German.
you'd be dead by now.

33
00:04:48.662 --> 00:04:53.210
But. may I introduce myself?
My name is Edgar waltz.

34
00:04:56.525 --> 00:04:57.631
Who are you hunting?

35
00:04:57.797 --> 00:04:59.174
His name is Ian Harmon.

36
00:04:59.340 --> 00:05:01.105
What's he done?

37
00:05:01.230 --> 00:05:02.206
He's a leader of the resistance.

38
00:05:03.397 --> 00:05:04.928
One of the few still alive.

39
00:05:05.053 --> 00:05:06.384
What's he done here in Portland?

40
00:05:06.509 --> 00:05:08.028
I don't know and I don't care.

41
00:05:08.153 --> 00:05:09.880
Time is of the essence
and I need to find him.

42
00:05:10.005 --> 00:05:13.918
We believe the resistance
has established a presence here

43
00:05:14.043 --> 00:05:17.121
to harbor fugitives
and make them disappear.

44
00:05:17.246 --> 00:05:19.023
The Verrat's problem
is with the resistance.

45
00:05:19.148 --> 00:05:20.374
They're not my problems.

46
00:05:20.499 --> 00:05:25.129
Maybe your past is not
as far away as you think.

47
00:05:25.254 --> 00:05:27.494
The Verrat does not make
decisions for me.

48
00:05:27.660 --> 00:05:29.454
The high command will not
be happy about that.

49
00:05:29.620 --> 00:05:30.914
I'm not concerned.

50
00:05:31.080 --> 00:05:32.870
It would be better for you
to be concerned about me

51
00:05:32.995 --> 00:05:35.001
and what will happen
should you refuse to help.

52
00:05:35.167 --> 00:05:38.046
I hope your Latin is as good
as your German.

53
00:05:38.212 --> 00:05:40.811
<i>Si vis pacem...</i>

54
00:05:40.936 --> 00:05:44.177
<i>Para bellum.</i>

55
00:05:44.343 --> 00:05:47.475
<i>Auf wiedersehen.</i> Captain.

56
00:05:59.922 --> 00:06:03.701
<i>"Si vis pacem. para bellum."</i>

57
00:06:03.826 --> 00:06:07.826
"If you seek peace. prepare for war."

58
00:06:13.622 --> 00:06:14.612
Thanks for picking him up.

59
00:06:14.737 --> 00:06:16.918
I don't get my car back
till tomorrow.

60
00:06:17.084 --> 00:06:18.795
- Coffee? Bacon?
- I usually take cream

61
00:06:18.961 --> 00:06:20.884
with my coffee. but I'll try bacon.

62
00:06:21.009 --> 00:06:22.119
I heard about you and adalind.

63
00:06:22.244 --> 00:06:24.855
We were together
for about half a cup of coffee.

64
00:06:24.980 --> 00:06:27.157
I don't know what happened.
where it came from.

65
00:06:27.282 --> 00:06:28.346
but I'm glad it's over.

66
00:06:28.512 --> 00:06:30.727
Well. between you and me.

67
00:06:30.852 --> 00:06:32.696
she was definitely
not good enough for you.

68
00:06:32.821 --> 00:06:35.061
If she wasn't a lawyer.
I'd think she roofied me.

69
00:06:35.227 --> 00:06:37.584
- What?
- I woke up. she was gone.

70
00:06:37.709 --> 00:06:40.942
And these two other people
who were in the room with me...

71
00:06:41.108 --> 00:06:43.007
It's more than I want to get into.

72
00:06:43.132 --> 00:06:46.364
I think it's more than I want you to.

73
00:06:46.530 --> 00:06:48.491
Whoa. whoa. whoa.

74
00:06:48.657 --> 00:06:50.160
- He is mine.
- All yours.

75
00:06:50.326 --> 00:06:51.745
- Mwah!
- See you tonight?

76
00:06:51.911 --> 00:06:53.751
We got a shooting at the bus depot.

77
00:06:53.876 --> 00:06:56.249
- Any bodies?
- Just blood.

78
00:06:56.415 --> 00:06:58.822
Yuck.

79
00:06:58.947 --> 00:07:02.683
- Watch your butts out there.
- We will.

80
00:07:16.552 --> 00:07:26.404
<font color="#3399FF">Sync and correction by Mlmlte</font>
<font color="#3399FF">www.addic7ed.com</font>

81
00:07:34.620 --> 00:07:36.122
{pub}Rosalee!

82
00:07:37.623 --> 00:07:40.043
Ian?
Oh. my God.

83
00:07:40.209 --> 00:07:41.836
- What happened to you?
- I was shot.

84
00:07:42.002 --> 00:07:43.887
I have to get you to a hospital.

85
00:07:44.012 --> 00:07:45.256
No. no. you can't.

86
00:07:45.422 --> 00:07:48.593
If they find out where I am.
I'm as good as dead.

87
00:07:48.718 --> 00:07:50.611
Where's Freddy?

88
00:07:50.736 --> 00:07:52.806
Freddy was killed.

89
00:07:52.972 --> 00:07:56.810
In a robbery. a few weeks ago.

90
00:07:56.976 --> 00:07:59.570
Freddy was supposed
to have some papers for me.

91
00:07:59.695 --> 00:08:01.772
That's why I'm here.

92
00:08:01.897 --> 00:08:02.941
Papers for what?

93
00:08:03.107 --> 00:08:04.943
A new identity.

94
00:08:05.109 --> 00:08:06.569
Who's trying to kill you?

95
00:08:06.735 --> 00:08:09.964
It's better if you don't know.
And it's better if I leave.

96
00:08:10.089 --> 00:08:12.099
You're not going anywhere.

97
00:08:12.224 --> 00:08:13.576
Not like this.

98
00:08:13.742 --> 00:08:14.719
Let me help you up.

99
00:08:14.844 --> 00:08:17.330
I'll get you something for the pain.

100
00:08:17.496 --> 00:08:18.373
I'm gonna get some help.

101
00:08:18.539 --> 00:08:21.459
Apparently the gunman
crossed the street here.

102
00:08:21.625 --> 00:08:23.093
Fired three times.

103
00:08:23.218 --> 00:08:24.695
Hence. broken car window.

104
00:08:24.820 --> 00:08:28.466
the defacing of our
friendly visitor greeting.

105
00:08:28.632 --> 00:08:31.594
Best guess is bloodstain belongs
to bullet number three.

106
00:08:31.760 --> 00:08:33.654
- So somebody got hit.
- But no body.

107
00:08:33.779 --> 00:08:36.507
Not yet.
Search is ongoing.

108
00:08:36.632 --> 00:08:38.576
No blood trail to follow.
so we cordoned off five blocks.

109
00:08:38.701 --> 00:08:40.228
Any description
of the shooter or the Vic?

110
00:08:40.394 --> 00:08:42.522
We got a witness at the bus
station. awaiting your arrival.

111
00:08:42.688 --> 00:08:47.335
Maybe surveillance tape.
And. uh. can I get that. please?

112
00:08:47.460 --> 00:08:51.622
This.

113
00:08:51.747 --> 00:08:53.283
9 millimeter.

114
00:08:53.449 --> 00:08:55.076
Yep. Let's check the witness.

115
00:08:55.242 --> 00:08:56.761
I didn't see the shooter.

116
00:08:56.886 --> 00:08:59.447
But I saw the guy that was on my bus.

117
00:08:59.572 --> 00:09:01.207
He left this hat on the seat.

118
00:09:01.373 --> 00:09:04.461
I tried to catch up with him.
but he was moving way too fast.

119
00:09:04.627 --> 00:09:06.470
Then I saw that car window shatter.

120
00:09:06.595 --> 00:09:08.256
I didn't know what the hell
was going on.

121
00:09:08.422 --> 00:09:09.841
Figured it was some kind
of gang thing.

122
00:09:10.007 --> 00:09:10.967
What can you tell us about him?

123
00:09:11.133 --> 00:09:14.137
His name.

124
00:09:14.303 --> 00:09:16.890
This is the ticket he used
to board the bus.

125
00:09:17.056 --> 00:09:19.450
Paid in cash.
Lester Cullum.

126
00:09:19.575 --> 00:09:21.227
Had one of those
old leather rucksacks.

127
00:09:21.393 --> 00:09:23.220
You don't see too many
of those anymore.

128
00:09:23.345 --> 00:09:25.732
British. I think.
He had an accent.

129
00:09:25.898 --> 00:09:29.152
Anyway. the name Lester Cullum
sounds kind of British.

130
00:09:38.160 --> 00:09:40.237
What's wrong?
I smell blood.

131
00:09:40.362 --> 00:09:42.022
I know.

132
00:09:42.147 --> 00:09:43.307
Come with me.

133
00:09:43.432 --> 00:09:45.009
Please tell me
this isn't another Zaubertrank.

134
00:09:45.134 --> 00:09:46.043
No. this one's a bullet.

135
00:09:46.168 --> 00:09:49.397
Well. look at that.

136
00:09:49.522 --> 00:09:52.400
Ian. this is my friend Monroe.

137
00:09:52.525 --> 00:09:53.885
Monroe. this is Ian.

138
00:09:54.051 --> 00:09:55.512
Hey.

139
00:09:55.678 --> 00:09:57.221
Is he a doctor?

140
00:09:57.346 --> 00:09:59.165
No. but he's gonna help me
get the bullet out.

141
00:09:59.290 --> 00:10:00.999
Why aren't we taking him
to a hospital?

142
00:10:01.124 --> 00:10:01.959
We can't.

143
00:10:02.084 --> 00:10:03.694
We have to do this now.

144
00:10:03.819 --> 00:10:06.648
I'm sorry. I don't entirely
understand the situation here.

145
00:10:06.814 --> 00:10:09.250
Ian is an old friend.
He's on the run.

146
00:10:09.375 --> 00:10:11.444
Someone tried to kill him.

147
00:10:11.610 --> 00:10:12.779
Well. what did he do?

148
00:10:12.945 --> 00:10:15.240
- Have you heard of the Lauffer?
- The Lauffer?

149
00:10:15.406 --> 00:10:16.724
You mean the resistance?
Yeah. sure.

150
00:10:16.849 --> 00:10:18.926
But that's not here.
that's old-country stuff.

151
00:10:19.051 --> 00:10:21.204
Well. it's here now.
That's Ian Harmon.

152
00:10:21.370 --> 00:10:24.982
- Have you heard of him?
- Really? The journalist?

153
00:10:25.107 --> 00:10:26.793
Yeah. well. he does that too.

154
00:10:26.959 --> 00:10:30.254
He's one of the leaders
of the resistance.

155
00:10:30.379 --> 00:10:32.406
So are we talking about the Verrat?

156
00:10:32.531 --> 00:10:34.801
- Because those guys are serious.
- I think so.

157
00:10:34.967 --> 00:10:36.444
Look. I cleaned the wound.

158
00:10:36.569 --> 00:10:39.639
I can see the bullet.
It's not that far in.

159
00:10:39.805 --> 00:10:41.516
And we're gonna get it out how?

160
00:10:41.682 --> 00:10:42.809
This was my father's.

161
00:10:42.975 --> 00:10:44.310
I used to watch him
do this kind of thing.

162
00:10:44.476 --> 00:10:46.704
I just don't want to do it alone.

163
00:10:46.829 --> 00:10:50.073
Okay.
What do you want me to do?

164
00:10:50.198 --> 00:10:51.815
Wash your hands.

165
00:10:51.940 --> 00:10:54.362
sterilize these.

166
00:10:54.528 --> 00:10:56.864
Upper right.
We should see him.

167
00:10:57.030 --> 00:11:00.285
That's got to be him.

168
00:11:00.451 --> 00:11:04.155
Average height.
average build. rucksack.

169
00:11:04.280 --> 00:11:05.206
That'll narrow it down.

170
00:11:05.372 --> 00:11:06.941
Any luck with the I.D.?

171
00:11:07.066 --> 00:11:09.210
I'm having a little trouble
connecting Lester Cullum

172
00:11:09.376 --> 00:11:10.545
to anybody.
It could be an alias.

173
00:11:10.711 --> 00:11:11.754
What about the bullet?

174
00:11:11.920 --> 00:11:13.798
They thought it was a regular
9 millimeter. It's not.

175
00:11:13.964 --> 00:11:16.367
According to ballistics.
the makeup of the brass

176
00:11:16.492 --> 00:11:19.203
identifies the company as
Deutsche Waffen munitions.

177
00:11:19.328 --> 00:11:20.738
who manufactured their bullets

178
00:11:20.863 --> 00:11:22.724
for their Luger
semi-automatic pistols.

179
00:11:22.890 --> 00:11:24.183
What is this. 1944?

180
00:11:24.349 --> 00:11:25.518
Actually. it was introduced in 1902.

181
00:11:25.684 --> 00:11:27.061
I think that eliminates
a gang shooting.

182
00:11:27.227 --> 00:11:29.246
More like a hit gone wrong.

183
00:11:29.371 --> 00:11:30.414
So we got a shooter on the loose.

184
00:11:30.539 --> 00:11:31.858
And nothing from the hospitals.

185
00:11:32.024 --> 00:11:34.861
Nobody showing up with bullet
wounds in the last 12 hours.

186
00:11:35.027 --> 00:11:36.195
We should check with
the St. Louis pd.

187
00:11:36.361 --> 00:11:37.739
where Lester Cullum boarded the bus.

188
00:11:38.246 --> 00:11:39.824
See if we can get
any hits on him there.

189
00:11:39.990 --> 00:11:41.225
If we've got a shooter
still out there

190
00:11:41.350 --> 00:11:42.726
and the guy he's after
is still alive.

191
00:11:42.851 --> 00:11:44.461
he's gonna try again.

192
00:11:44.586 --> 00:11:45.529
What the hell did you do that for?

193
00:11:45.654 --> 00:11:47.264
Bring it right here. right here!

194
00:11:49.441 --> 00:11:51.085
Get off!

195
00:11:53.253 --> 00:11:54.471
Hey. knock it off.

196
00:11:56.298 --> 00:11:58.209
I said. "knock it off"!

197
00:12:06.108 --> 00:12:07.518
Idiots.

198
00:12:07.684 --> 00:12:10.146
Sorry about that. buddy.

199
00:12:10.312 --> 00:12:12.623
Got one on the house for you.

200
00:12:12.748 --> 00:12:14.091
Oh. thank you.

201
00:12:14.216 --> 00:12:15.442
Won't break me.

202
00:12:15.567 --> 00:12:20.073
Very kind.

203
00:12:20.239 --> 00:12:22.742
Look. I'm in kind of a jam.

204
00:12:22.908 --> 00:12:24.668
I was wondering if you know
of any place

205
00:12:24.793 --> 00:12:26.496
where they make some kind of papers.

206
00:12:26.996 --> 00:12:31.041
I'm a little out of date.
You know what I mean?

207
00:12:31.166 --> 00:12:32.877
What kind of papers you looking for?

208
00:12:33.043 --> 00:12:37.423
You know. something
that will get me out of here.

209
00:12:37.589 --> 00:12:42.119
- Passport stuff.
- Yes.

210
00:12:42.244 --> 00:12:44.622
Uh...

211
00:12:44.747 --> 00:12:48.142
Oh. this guy's good.

212
00:12:48.308 --> 00:12:50.978
- He's just downtown.
- Oh.

213
00:12:51.144 --> 00:12:53.864
Yes. uh. are you sure he's the best?

214
00:12:53.989 --> 00:12:55.900
'Cause I can't afford
to get caught again.

215
00:12:56.066 --> 00:12:58.528
Anybody in town like us
needs a job like that.

216
00:12:58.694 --> 00:13:01.722
- he's the one.
- Good. good. Thank you.

217
00:13:01.847 --> 00:13:05.225
Thank you very much.

218
00:13:05.350 --> 00:13:09.330
Oh. better not leave this.

219
00:13:14.276 --> 00:13:17.588
How is it they allow
a Lausenschlange to serve food?

220
00:13:17.754 --> 00:13:22.343
What?

221
00:13:22.509 --> 00:13:24.595
Hundjager.

222
00:13:24.761 --> 00:13:27.231
What do you want?

223
00:13:27.356 --> 00:13:28.990
A dead man.

224
00:13:32.640 --> 00:13:33.921
{pub}Anybody knows the truth

225
00:13:34.046 --> 00:13:35.720
about who he is.
what he's running from?

226
00:13:35.845 --> 00:13:37.138
Any of it?

227
00:13:37.263 --> 00:13:38.356
He was a friend of Freddy's.

228
00:13:38.481 --> 00:13:40.945
Look don't get me wrong.
I liked Freddy.

229
00:13:41.111 --> 00:13:43.995
But he was involved with
some seriously shady people.

230
00:13:44.120 --> 00:13:45.533
Freddy made some mistakes.

231
00:13:45.699 --> 00:13:47.799
Just like we all do.

232
00:13:47.924 --> 00:13:51.164
But I knew him too.

233
00:13:51.330 --> 00:13:52.665
Well enough to trust him?

234
00:13:52.831 --> 00:13:55.306
I was...

235
00:13:55.431 --> 00:13:57.879
With him for a year and a half.

236
00:13:58.045 --> 00:14:00.545
Oh.

237
00:14:00.670 --> 00:14:01.799
We're talking more than just...

238
00:14:01.965 --> 00:14:05.249
Yes.
It was a long time ago.

239
00:14:05.374 --> 00:14:10.471
Can I ask what happened?

240
00:14:10.596 --> 00:14:12.557
He left.

241
00:14:12.682 --> 00:14:14.270
I wasn't happy about it.

242
00:14:14.436 --> 00:14:18.441
But that is all in the past.

243
00:14:25.895 --> 00:14:29.307
Look. if someone is really
trying to kill this guy.

244
00:14:29.432 --> 00:14:31.329
we should call Nick.

245
00:14:31.495 --> 00:14:32.577
I mean. I don't know what he'll say

246
00:14:32.702 --> 00:14:34.123
about being introduced to a Grimm.

247
00:14:34.289 --> 00:14:35.480
but right now.

248
00:14:35.605 --> 00:14:37.081
this guy doesn't have a lot
to say about anything.

249
00:14:37.206 --> 00:14:41.235
Rosalee.

250
00:14:42.545 --> 00:14:45.176
- I'm here.
- Rosalee.

251
00:15:05.268 --> 00:15:07.865
The same casing as the bus station.

252
00:15:08.031 --> 00:15:10.535
9x19-millimeter parabellum.

253
00:15:10.701 --> 00:15:12.617
Single bullet to the head.
No muss. no fuss.

254
00:15:12.742 --> 00:15:13.996
Killer came in here with a plan.

255
00:15:14.162 --> 00:15:15.987
Which looks like
"get the money and get out."

256
00:15:16.112 --> 00:15:19.023
He might have tried to fight back.

257
00:15:19.148 --> 00:15:22.076
A passport here.

258
00:15:22.201 --> 00:15:27.465
"Ian Harmon."

259
00:15:27.590 --> 00:15:30.805
Huh. Kind of looks like
the guy the bus driver I.D.'d.

260
00:15:30.971 --> 00:15:32.515
wasn't he the victim?

261
00:15:32.681 --> 00:15:34.225
- Victims need money too.
- Hey. sarge?

262
00:15:34.391 --> 00:15:35.768
Yeah.

263
00:15:35.934 --> 00:15:36.974
We got
a possible witness out front.

264
00:15:37.099 --> 00:15:38.020
Okay. hold him.

265
00:15:38.186 --> 00:15:39.810
Got a possible witness outside.

266
00:15:39.935 --> 00:15:43.714
- Who wants him?
- Got it.

267
00:15:43.839 --> 00:15:46.350
Hi. I'm Detective Burkhardt.

268
00:15:46.475 --> 00:15:47.985
Oh. hi. hi Detective.

269
00:15:48.110 --> 00:15:51.742
I was across the street
and I saw this man come running.

270
00:15:51.908 --> 00:15:52.723
and didn't think anything
of it at first.

271
00:15:52.848 --> 00:15:54.859
And then the police cars came here

272
00:15:54.984 --> 00:15:56.914
and they told me
the bartender was shot.

273
00:15:57.080 --> 00:15:58.916
Do you think you could identify
the man you saw?

274
00:15:59.082 --> 00:16:01.878
If I saw him again. maybe. yeah.

275
00:16:02.044 --> 00:16:03.367
Did you...
Did you arrest anybody?

276
00:16:03.492 --> 00:16:05.965
Not yet. no.

277
00:16:06.131 --> 00:16:11.554
Is this the man you saw?

278
00:16:11.720 --> 00:16:13.931
Just take it easy.

279
00:16:14.097 --> 00:16:16.747
I'm sorry. I was just trying to help.

280
00:16:16.872 --> 00:16:21.606
I just want to know
if this is the man you saw.

281
00:16:21.772 --> 00:16:24.155
Yes. sir. yeah.
that's him. that's him.

282
00:16:24.280 --> 00:16:26.891
All right.
Gonna need your name and number.

283
00:16:27.016 --> 00:16:28.826
just in case we need
confirmation on the I.D.

284
00:16:28.951 --> 00:16:30.031
Yes. of course.

285
00:16:30.197 --> 00:16:31.657
Max Kurtz.
K-u-r...

286
00:16:31.823 --> 00:16:35.578
Drink this.

287
00:16:36.258 --> 00:16:38.986
Look. I hope you warned your friend

288
00:16:39.111 --> 00:16:41.172
that it could be very dangerous

289
00:16:41.297 --> 00:16:44.709
for either of you
to be wherever I am.

290
00:16:44.834 --> 00:16:47.495
Hey. you want to meet someone
who's dangerous to be around?

291
00:16:47.620 --> 00:16:49.213
Should meet my friend Nick.

292
00:16:49.338 --> 00:16:51.761
He's a...
He's a friend who...

293
00:16:51.927 --> 00:16:53.554
He can...
Well. uh...

294
00:16:53.720 --> 00:16:56.140
- He's a Grimm.
- Well. okay.

295
00:16:56.306 --> 00:16:58.142
So much for the hemming and hawing.

296
00:16:58.308 --> 00:16:59.857
- Are you serious?
- Actually. yes. very.

297
00:16:59.982 --> 00:17:01.692
But. look. he's not
what you've ever heard about.

298
00:17:01.817 --> 00:17:03.481
He's right.
Nick is not what you'd expect.

299
00:17:03.647 --> 00:17:06.067
He caught the men responsible
for killing Freddy.

300
00:17:06.233 --> 00:17:07.682
And he helped me
when I first got here

301
00:17:07.807 --> 00:17:12.403
and had to deal with his murder
and the shop and everything.

302
00:17:12.528 --> 00:17:15.701
And he got Monroe to help me
when it was dangerous for me.

303
00:17:15.867 --> 00:17:16.874
Monroe's been helping me ever since.

304
00:17:16.999 --> 00:17:18.943
And how much did you have
to pay this Grimm

305
00:17:19.068 --> 00:17:20.711
to go after
the man who killed Freddy?

306
00:17:20.836 --> 00:17:22.380
I didn't have to pay him anything.

307
00:17:22.505 --> 00:17:25.950
Yeah. um. that's the other shoe.

308
00:17:26.075 --> 00:17:27.129
He's a cop.

309
00:17:27.295 --> 00:17:29.090
I know.

310
00:17:29.256 --> 00:17:31.509
My first encounter with him
wasn't exactly friendly.

311
00:17:31.675 --> 00:17:34.136
But let me tell you.
Nick is the real deal.

312
00:17:34.302 --> 00:17:35.793
And if you need help
in this town. he is the <i>man.</i>

313
00:17:35.918 --> 00:17:37.640
Or the Grimm.

314
00:17:37.806 --> 00:17:40.184
I know it's a lot to fathom.

315
00:17:40.350 --> 00:17:42.478
but he's friends with a Blutbad.

316
00:17:42.644 --> 00:17:44.563
And a Fuchsbau.

317
00:17:44.729 --> 00:17:48.189
Listen. dude. he has saved my ass

318
00:17:48.483 --> 00:17:49.694
and I've saved his.

319
00:17:49.860 --> 00:17:53.364
Believe it or not. he's just
trying to do the right thing.

320
00:17:53.530 --> 00:17:54.949
Do you know about the resistance?

321
00:17:55.115 --> 00:17:55.950
Yeah.

322
00:17:56.116 --> 00:17:57.181
Do you know who the Verrat sends

323
00:17:57.306 --> 00:17:58.661
after anyone associated with it?

324
00:17:58.827 --> 00:18:00.913
No.

325
00:18:01.079 --> 00:18:03.120
Hundjager.

326
00:18:03.245 --> 00:18:05.418
That is so not good.

327
00:18:05.584 --> 00:18:08.462
Rosalee. do you trust this man?

328
00:18:08.628 --> 00:18:10.661
I do.

329
00:18:10.786 --> 00:18:15.433
Well. then. by all means.

330
00:18:15.558 --> 00:18:17.430
put my life in his hands.

331
00:18:17.596 --> 00:18:19.370
Possible motive
for killing the bartender

332
00:18:19.495 --> 00:18:20.571
was the money in the register.

333
00:18:20.696 --> 00:18:22.351
But our suspect
was supposed to be wounded

334
00:18:22.517 --> 00:18:24.562
- when he got off the bus.
- Could explain his desperation.

335
00:18:24.728 --> 00:18:26.644
Any identification
on the man who shot Harmon?

336
00:18:26.769 --> 00:18:27.690
Nothing.
He wasn't on the bus.

337
00:18:27.856 --> 00:18:29.853
didn't show up
on surveillance cameras.

338
00:18:29.978 --> 00:18:31.882
The bar didn't have any security
except the alarm and...

339
00:18:32.007 --> 00:18:32.862
It was off.

340
00:18:33.175 --> 00:18:35.114
Let's pull out all the stops.

341
00:18:35.280 --> 00:18:36.574
Find the one we know... Harmon.

342
00:18:36.740 --> 00:18:38.826
Hopefully. he'll lead us
to whoever shot him.

343
00:18:38.992 --> 00:18:40.060
- Yes. sir.
- And check with Scotland yard.

344
00:18:40.185 --> 00:18:41.579
See if they have
any record on Harmon.

345
00:18:41.745 --> 00:18:44.862
Might help us identify
who this other man is.

346
00:18:46.249 --> 00:18:48.419
Yeah. Burkhardt.

347
00:18:48.585 --> 00:18:50.584
Could you get down
to the spice shop asap?

348
00:18:50.709 --> 00:18:52.787
Why? What's going on?

349
00:18:52.912 --> 00:18:54.759
It's kind of complicated.
There's a man here.

350
00:18:54.925 --> 00:18:56.073
He's like
a civil rights activist. slash...

351
00:18:56.198 --> 00:18:57.925
I don't know...
Freedom fighter.

352
00:18:58.050 --> 00:18:59.346
With a bullet wound.

353
00:18:59.512 --> 00:19:02.141
Yeah. I'll be right there.

354
00:19:06.542 --> 00:19:08.481
Yeah.

355
00:19:08.647 --> 00:19:09.553
Wie geht's Captain.

356
00:19:09.678 --> 00:19:11.942
- How is your day?
- Where are you?

357
00:19:12.108 --> 00:19:15.025
I'm enjoying your city.
It's really quite nice.

358
00:19:15.150 --> 00:19:17.948
It reminds me a little of Firenze.

359
00:19:18.114 --> 00:19:21.744
So have you made any progress on
that terrible murder at the bar?

360
00:19:21.910 --> 00:19:24.135
You laid out the evidence
a little too obviously

361
00:19:24.260 --> 00:19:25.369
for my taste.

362
00:19:25.494 --> 00:19:26.737
Well. if you'd helped me
when I asked.

363
00:19:26.862 --> 00:19:28.292
we wouldn't be having
this conversation right now.

364
00:19:28.458 --> 00:19:31.045
You needed a reason to find Ian.
and now you have it.

365
00:19:31.211 --> 00:19:33.214
I'm glad you're taking him
seriously now.

366
00:19:33.619 --> 00:19:37.415
You never know when a desperate
man like that will strike again.

367
00:19:37.540 --> 00:19:39.678
Oh. by the way. I liked
your Detective Burkhardt.

368
00:19:39.844 --> 00:19:41.352
There's more to him
than meets the eye.

369
00:19:41.477 --> 00:19:42.503
What do you want?

370
00:19:42.628 --> 00:19:43.557
I want to know why you didn't tell me

371
00:19:43.723 --> 00:19:46.102
that you had a Grimm working for you.

372
00:19:46.268 --> 00:19:47.853
He could be very useful to me.

373
00:19:48.019 --> 00:19:49.313
Why don't you make that happen?

374
00:19:49.479 --> 00:19:50.761
He doesn't know about me.

375
00:19:50.886 --> 00:19:53.097
Then you are playing
a very dangerous game.

376
00:19:53.222 --> 00:19:57.696
my dear Captain.

377
00:19:57.862 --> 00:20:01.763
"Reginald's camera." Okay.

378
00:20:08.370 --> 00:20:10.281
- Beautiful. aren't they?
- Oh. yes. yes.

379
00:20:10.406 --> 00:20:13.234
I mean. the Leica II
belongs in a museum.

380
00:20:13.359 --> 00:20:16.587
And the Voigtlander...
Very nice. very nice.

381
00:20:16.712 --> 00:20:18.217
I would say you must be from Germany.

382
00:20:18.383 --> 00:20:20.508
Yes. yes.
I think my accent gets thicker

383
00:20:20.633 --> 00:20:23.139
when I look at German cameras.

384
00:20:23.305 --> 00:20:24.628
Well. feel free to look around.

385
00:20:24.753 --> 00:20:26.630
I like to think of this shop
as my own private museum.

386
00:20:26.755 --> 00:20:29.099
Oh. thank you. thank you.
Yes. yes.

387
00:20:29.224 --> 00:20:31.552
Oh. beautiful.
Look at that.

388
00:20:31.677 --> 00:20:34.567
These pictures.
Did you take them?

389
00:20:34.733 --> 00:20:36.006
- Yes.
- Oh.

390
00:20:36.131 --> 00:20:37.236
That's my daughter Julia.

391
00:20:37.402 --> 00:20:38.876
- Yes?
- And her kids...

392
00:20:39.001 --> 00:20:40.227
Emily. Tommy and Joey.

393
00:20:40.352 --> 00:20:42.658
Tommy. Joey too.
Oh. gorgeous.

394
00:20:42.824 --> 00:20:46.036
Look at the quality
of the light and the detail.

395
00:20:46.202 --> 00:20:48.539
All this digital nonsense
has no sense of depth.

396
00:20:48.705 --> 00:20:51.292
No. no. no.
Do you collect?

397
00:20:51.458 --> 00:20:55.629
Not cameras.
Let me show you my favorite.

398
00:20:57.547 --> 00:21:03.133
This is a 1926 Luger po8 9 millimeter

399
00:21:03.258 --> 00:21:04.301
with a silencer.

400
00:21:04.426 --> 00:21:07.933
It's been in my family
for generations.

401
00:21:08.099 --> 00:21:09.143
It works perfectly.

402
00:21:09.309 --> 00:21:10.707
I can't say I'm a big fan of guns.

403
00:21:10.832 --> 00:21:11.942
I can imagine.

404
00:21:12.067 --> 00:21:13.978
Especially when
you have something to hide.

405
00:21:14.103 --> 00:21:15.636
I don't know
what you're talking about.

406
00:21:15.761 --> 00:21:17.381
Let me tell you.

407
00:21:17.506 --> 00:21:19.984
You might shoot photographs
of your family.

408
00:21:20.109 --> 00:21:21.585
well. I will just shoot them.

409
00:21:21.710 --> 00:21:25.659
Unless you decide that they
are worth more than lying to me.

410
00:21:25.825 --> 00:21:29.371
Yes? Good. Good.

411
00:21:29.537 --> 00:21:31.790
We understand each other.

412
00:21:31.956 --> 00:21:33.959
- Huh. Reginald?
- What do you want?

413
00:21:34.125 --> 00:21:38.402
Oh. yes.
Let me show you.

414
00:21:38.527 --> 00:21:40.216
Have you seen this man?

415
00:21:40.382 --> 00:21:42.673
Come on.

416
00:21:45.718 --> 00:21:48.012
Good. you made it.

417
00:21:52.875 --> 00:21:54.969
Rosalee called me this morning.
early.

418
00:21:55.094 --> 00:21:56.523
She said she had some kind of
breaking and entering problem.

419
00:21:56.689 --> 00:21:57.855
You said "bullet wound."

420
00:21:57.980 --> 00:21:59.106
Yeah. I know.

421
00:21:59.231 --> 00:22:03.739
Hang on. I'm getting to that.

422
00:22:04.406 --> 00:22:05.991
- Don't move.
- Whoa!

423
00:22:06.533 --> 00:22:07.785
Nick!
Nick. wait! Wait.

424
00:22:07.951 --> 00:22:11.997
This man's wanted for murder.

425
00:22:12.163 --> 00:22:14.291
Well I guess he's just trying
to do the right thing.

426
00:22:19.935 --> 00:22:22.587
{pub}I've found his passport
next to the bartender that he shot.

427
00:22:22.712 --> 00:22:24.802
Ian lost his bag when he was shot.

428
00:22:24.968 --> 00:22:26.762
That's how the guy
who shot him got his passport.

429
00:22:26.928 --> 00:22:27.763
That's what he told you?

430
00:22:27.929 --> 00:22:29.431
When was this bartender shot?

431
00:22:29.597 --> 00:22:31.866
- Four hours ago.
- Then it can't be him. Nick.

432
00:22:31.991 --> 00:22:33.268
We've been with him
for longer than that.

433
00:22:33.435 --> 00:22:35.804
Ian's been here since
I opened the shop this morning.

434
00:22:35.929 --> 00:22:38.565
Clearly he wants you
to find me because he can't.

435
00:22:38.731 --> 00:22:40.818
That's why he shot this bartender.

436
00:22:40.984 --> 00:22:42.611
If you arrest me right now.

437
00:22:42.736 --> 00:22:45.322
then he'll know exactly where I am.

438
00:22:45.488 --> 00:22:47.316
- Did you check him for weapons?
- He doesn't have any.

439
00:22:47.441 --> 00:22:49.868
He came here because my brother
was supposed to help him.

440
00:22:56.182 --> 00:23:00.170
Well. Nick Burkhardt.
meet Ian Harmon.

441
00:23:00.336 --> 00:23:03.549
- Ian. Nick.
- A pleasure.

442
00:23:04.658 --> 00:23:06.719
The man who's trying
to kill you. what's his name?

443
00:23:06.885 --> 00:23:07.928
Edgar waltz.

444
00:23:08.803 --> 00:23:09.805
He's an enforcer for the Verrat.

445
00:23:10.764 --> 00:23:13.058
Verrat? I thought
they only operated in Europe.

446
00:23:13.224 --> 00:23:15.410
Their influence is spreading.

447
00:23:15.535 --> 00:23:18.046
They occupy positions
of power everywhere...

448
00:23:18.171 --> 00:23:21.066
Politics. industry. organized crime.

449
00:23:21.232 --> 00:23:25.520
Anything that is corruptible is
susceptible to their influence.

450
00:23:25.645 --> 00:23:26.697
Even law enforcement.

451
00:23:26.863 --> 00:23:28.790
Nick. these guys make
the Spanish inquisition

452
00:23:28.915 --> 00:23:30.701
look like the SPCA.

453
00:23:30.867 --> 00:23:33.787
And Ian's resistance group...
The Lauffer...

454
00:23:33.953 --> 00:23:35.789
Is the only thing
that stands in their way.

455
00:23:35.955 --> 00:23:38.709
This world is on the brink of war.

456
00:23:38.875 --> 00:23:41.570
The turmoil in the middle east.

457
00:23:41.695 --> 00:23:43.505
the crises in Europe.

458
00:23:43.671 --> 00:23:44.956
the Arab spring...

459
00:23:45.081 --> 00:23:48.076
All of it is tied together.

460
00:23:48.201 --> 00:23:51.847
Agents of the Verrat.
working for the seven houses.

461
00:23:52.013 --> 00:23:55.884
have infiltrated the highest
levels of all governments.

462
00:23:56.009 --> 00:23:59.187
- The seven houses?
- The seven royal families.

463
00:23:59.354 --> 00:24:01.590
This is not a new struggle.

464
00:24:01.715 --> 00:24:03.558
It's been going on for centuries.

465
00:24:03.683 --> 00:24:07.062
With this struggle. the royal
families recognize opportunities

466
00:24:07.187 --> 00:24:09.398
to gain more control.

467
00:24:09.523 --> 00:24:12.968
People. driven by fear.
choose stability over freedom.

468
00:24:13.093 --> 00:24:14.436
when their neighbors start to die.

469
00:24:14.561 --> 00:24:16.705
My parents were part
of the resistance

470
00:24:16.871 --> 00:24:19.458
and my grandparents. my brother.

471
00:24:19.624 --> 00:24:20.942
I never wanted to be involved.

472
00:24:21.067 --> 00:24:23.779
It always seemed so far away.

473
00:24:23.904 --> 00:24:26.748
Your people changed
the balance of power

474
00:24:26.873 --> 00:24:30.151
when they decided
to work for the royal families.

475
00:24:30.276 --> 00:24:31.678
I don't know
what you're talking about.

476
00:24:31.844 --> 00:24:33.555
Grimms.

477
00:24:33.680 --> 00:24:36.508
Evidently you don't even know
how valuable you are

478
00:24:36.633 --> 00:24:37.959
to the royals.

479
00:24:38.084 --> 00:24:39.761
Look...

480
00:24:39.886 --> 00:24:41.513
I don't mean to be insensitive.

481
00:24:41.638 --> 00:24:44.608
but right now I'm trying
to find a murderer.

482
00:24:44.774 --> 00:24:46.802
not get a Wesen history lesson.

483
00:24:46.927 --> 00:24:48.937
Nick. Ian needs your help.

484
00:24:49.062 --> 00:24:51.373
We have to get him out
of here before waltz finds him.

485
00:24:51.498 --> 00:24:52.908
The only reason he's not dead.

486
00:24:53.074 --> 00:24:55.310
is because the bullet
went through his pack first.

487
00:24:55.435 --> 00:24:56.620
But he lost his papers.

488
00:24:56.786 --> 00:25:01.249
And without them. he can't leave.

489
00:25:01.374 --> 00:25:03.068
Are you talking
about getting false documents

490
00:25:03.193 --> 00:25:05.687
to get him out of the country?

491
00:25:05.812 --> 00:25:06.922
I'm sorry.

492
00:25:07.088 --> 00:25:09.357
This just keeps getting
better and better.

493
00:25:09.482 --> 00:25:12.194
Rosalee's brother was
the last stop for Wesen trying

494
00:25:12.319 --> 00:25:13.679
to get out of the country.

495
00:25:13.845 --> 00:25:15.597
He was going to help me.

496
00:25:15.722 --> 00:25:18.767
All right. look.
if all of this is true.

497
00:25:18.892 --> 00:25:20.469
then the most important thing
for me to do

498
00:25:20.594 --> 00:25:22.187
is to find Edgar waltz.

499
00:25:22.353 --> 00:25:25.040
I can't promise anything else yet.

500
00:25:25.165 --> 00:25:27.818
Okay. yeah.
Fair enough.

501
00:25:27.984 --> 00:25:30.571
- Does waltz know about Freddy?
- No.

502
00:25:30.737 --> 00:25:33.574
If he did. I would be dead by now.

503
00:25:33.740 --> 00:25:35.150
And so would they.

504
00:25:35.275 --> 00:25:39.688
Okay. stay here for now.

505
00:25:39.813 --> 00:25:42.056
Do you know where
you can get him new papers?

506
00:25:42.181 --> 00:25:43.291
I think so.

507
00:25:43.416 --> 00:25:45.419
We were looking through the shop
and found a bunch

508
00:25:45.585 --> 00:25:46.945
of fake passports of my brother's.

509
00:25:47.070 --> 00:25:49.173
I know that man who did them.
His name is Reginald.

510
00:25:49.339 --> 00:25:51.232
Don't tell me anymore. okay?

511
00:25:51.357 --> 00:25:53.302
I'll call you when I get something.

512
00:25:53.468 --> 00:25:56.597
- Thanks. Nick.
- Yeah.

513
00:26:02.419 --> 00:26:04.613
May I help you?

514
00:26:04.738 --> 00:26:06.515
My brother sent me.

515
00:26:06.640 --> 00:26:08.133
Who?

516
00:26:08.258 --> 00:26:09.885
Freddy.

517
00:26:10.010 --> 00:26:11.119
I know you helped him.

518
00:26:11.244 --> 00:26:12.437
And now I need your help.

519
00:26:12.562 --> 00:26:13.788
Please.

520
00:26:13.913 --> 00:26:15.257
What do you want?

521
00:26:15.382 --> 00:26:16.691
A passport.

522
00:26:16.816 --> 00:26:17.993
I...

523
00:26:18.159 --> 00:26:19.411
Do you know who this is?

524
00:26:19.577 --> 00:26:21.079
I can't.

525
00:26:21.245 --> 00:26:22.581
He's been shot.

526
00:26:22.747 --> 00:26:24.282
He came to Freddy for help.

527
00:26:24.407 --> 00:26:30.297
I'm helping him now.

528
00:26:30.463 --> 00:26:34.366
I don't know where else to go.

529
00:26:36.786 --> 00:26:38.222
I'm gonna need some time.

530
00:26:41.307 --> 00:26:48.148
♪ ♪

531
00:26:56.956 --> 00:26:57.983
After being told
of their arrest

532
00:26:58.108 --> 00:26:59.484
I was able to get close enough
with my camera.

533
00:26:59.609 --> 00:27:00.635
for the first time.

534
00:27:00.760 --> 00:27:02.571
to the place where they took the men.

535
00:27:02.696 --> 00:27:05.323
The Verrat enforcers executed farmers

536
00:27:05.448 --> 00:27:08.360
associated with the Spanish Republic.

537
00:27:08.485 --> 00:27:10.712
These enforcers infiltrated
the highest ranks

538
00:27:10.837 --> 00:27:12.798
of the monarchists and Franco's army.

539
00:27:13.623 --> 00:27:19.263
They exacted Verrat law.
across the land. with impunity.

540
00:27:19.429 --> 00:27:20.488
Accused of stealing.

541
00:27:20.613 --> 00:27:22.766
these innocent Wesen
were executed without trial.

542
00:27:22.932 --> 00:27:26.228
Their true crime was marrying
outside their own breed.

543
00:27:26.394 --> 00:27:28.964
The Verrat enforcers were
identified as Hundjager.

544
00:27:29.089 --> 00:27:31.383
from a race so tenacious and vicious

545
00:27:31.508 --> 00:27:34.135
that it is said they are birthed
by consuming their own mothers

546
00:27:34.260 --> 00:27:37.272
from inside the womb.

547
00:27:37.397 --> 00:27:42.401
Edvard Grimm. Madrid. 1936.

548
00:27:55.782 --> 00:27:57.375
Yeah. Burkhardt.

549
00:27:57.500 --> 00:27:59.052
Hello. Detective.

550
00:27:59.218 --> 00:28:00.929
Let me introduce myself.
I'm Edgar waltz.

551
00:28:01.095 --> 00:28:03.999
Apparently you and I
have something in common.

552
00:28:04.124 --> 00:28:05.900
We're both looking for Ian Harmon.

553
00:28:06.025 --> 00:28:07.769
Where are you?

554
00:28:07.935 --> 00:28:10.905
Do you know the terms
of a Freidenreden?

555
00:28:11.030 --> 00:28:14.092
Uh. yeah.

556
00:28:14.217 --> 00:28:18.103
So let's just say.
um. union station. 10:00.

557
00:28:21.157 --> 00:28:22.317
And how will I know you?

558
00:28:22.442 --> 00:28:25.454
Oh. I don't think that will
be a problem. Detective.

559
00:28:32.786 --> 00:28:34.763
Are you always this animated?

560
00:28:34.888 --> 00:28:37.049
Well. you made me miss my yoga.

561
00:28:37.215 --> 00:28:39.117
So...

562
00:28:39.242 --> 00:28:41.369
You care about Rosalee.

563
00:28:41.494 --> 00:28:43.038
I do.

564
00:28:43.163 --> 00:28:45.573
I care about all my friends.
even the ones you don't like.

565
00:28:45.698 --> 00:28:50.011
I don't dislike him.
he's just a Grimm.

566
00:28:50.136 --> 00:28:51.438
Well. we're all equals.

567
00:28:52.005 --> 00:28:54.816
Isn't that what you're fighting for?

568
00:28:59.813 --> 00:29:01.022
Yeah.

569
00:29:01.147 --> 00:29:02.724
What?

570
00:29:02.849 --> 00:29:04.284
Hang on. hang on.

571
00:29:04.450 --> 00:29:07.287
You ever heard of a "Freidenreden"?

572
00:29:07.453 --> 00:29:09.531
- Who is that?
- It's Nick.

573
00:29:09.656 --> 00:29:13.151
Put him on speaker.

574
00:29:13.276 --> 00:29:15.937
Yeah. you're on speaker
with me and Ian.

575
00:29:16.062 --> 00:29:17.589
Who asked you about a Freidenreden?

576
00:29:17.755 --> 00:29:19.007
Waltz called me.

577
00:29:19.173 --> 00:29:20.975
Does he know you found me?

578
00:29:21.100 --> 00:29:22.944
No. I don't think so.

579
00:29:23.069 --> 00:29:25.722
He wants me to meet him at 10:00 P.M.

580
00:29:25.888 --> 00:29:27.949
He asked me if I knew
what a Freidenreden was.

581
00:29:28.074 --> 00:29:29.317
I said I did. but I don't.

582
00:29:29.442 --> 00:29:31.353
It's a truce...
A white-flag meeting.

583
00:29:31.519 --> 00:29:34.690
You both come unarmed and you
both leave of your own accord.

584
00:29:34.856 --> 00:29:35.974
Dude. you can't seriously be thinking

585
00:29:36.099 --> 00:29:37.442
of meeting this guy unarmed.

586
00:29:37.608 --> 00:29:38.827
He will honor it.

587
00:29:38.952 --> 00:29:40.862
They have a great belief
in the sanctity of rules.

588
00:29:41.028 --> 00:29:42.630
Nick. one more thing.

589
00:29:42.755 --> 00:29:45.617
Once the truce is over...
The minute you walk away...

590
00:29:45.783 --> 00:29:46.835
Anything goes.

591
00:29:46.960 --> 00:29:49.771
So watch your back.

592
00:29:53.433 --> 00:29:55.267
Waltz is getting closer.

593
00:29:55.887 --> 00:29:57.671
This place isn't safe anymore.

594
00:30:11.138 --> 00:30:12.811
{pub}Detective Burkhardt.

595
00:30:17.982 --> 00:30:19.666
I admire punctuality.

596
00:30:19.791 --> 00:30:22.141
Hands out of your pockets. please.

597
00:30:23.045 --> 00:30:24.345
Well. you too.

598
00:30:30.134 --> 00:30:31.872
So I guess you really did
witness the murder

599
00:30:32.038 --> 00:30:33.123
of the bartender.

600
00:30:33.289 --> 00:30:36.126
Yes. I really did.

601
00:30:36.292 --> 00:30:38.218
Just so you know. once this
little truce of yours is over.

602
00:30:38.343 --> 00:30:39.713
I'm arresting your ass for murder.

603
00:30:41.112 --> 00:30:44.259
If you try to arrest me.
you'd better be armed.

604
00:30:44.425 --> 00:30:47.596
which means you violated the rules.

605
00:30:47.762 --> 00:30:49.806
I don't give a damn about your rules.

606
00:30:49.972 --> 00:30:52.934
I brought mine too.

607
00:30:53.100 --> 00:30:54.686
Rules are meant to be broken.

608
00:30:54.852 --> 00:30:56.736
aren't they. Detective?

609
00:30:56.861 --> 00:30:59.524
But before you get
all bold and brash.

610
00:30:59.690 --> 00:31:01.074
take a look around

611
00:31:01.199 --> 00:31:05.405
and count the number of innocent
victims that will die

612
00:31:05.571 --> 00:31:07.480
if you attempt to arrest me.

613
00:31:07.605 --> 00:31:09.409
So let's not waste time.

614
00:31:09.575 --> 00:31:11.787
I want Ian Harmon. you can find him.

615
00:31:11.953 --> 00:31:13.103
So you can murder him.

616
00:31:13.228 --> 00:31:15.321
You're a Grimm.
I'm a Hundjager.

617
00:31:15.446 --> 00:31:17.023
We're not friends. but. uh...

618
00:31:17.148 --> 00:31:20.212
We've always been...
How shall I put it...

619
00:31:20.378 --> 00:31:22.047
Allies of convenience.

620
00:31:22.213 --> 00:31:23.715
Not around here we haven't.

621
00:31:23.881 --> 00:31:28.118
If you don't help me
find my prey within 24 hours.

622
00:31:28.243 --> 00:31:32.272
you will be finding dead bodies
all over the city.

623
00:31:33.808 --> 00:31:35.894
Would you excuse me for a moment?

624
00:31:36.060 --> 00:31:38.545
Thank you.
Yeah?

625
00:31:38.670 --> 00:31:40.780
There's a woman here.

626
00:31:40.905 --> 00:31:42.916
She's asking for a passport.
like you said.

627
00:31:43.041 --> 00:31:47.044
Good. Keep the package
until I get there.

628
00:31:49.657 --> 00:31:52.675
Oh. and if you attempt to follow me.

629
00:31:52.800 --> 00:31:55.789
I will shoot the first person I see.

630
00:31:55.955 --> 00:31:59.167
Good night.

631
00:32:03.895 --> 00:32:05.238
The killer called you?

632
00:32:05.363 --> 00:32:07.473
Yes. Wu is running
the number right now.

633
00:32:07.598 --> 00:32:09.177
He said his name is Edgar waltz.

634
00:32:09.343 --> 00:32:11.143
He admitted to killing the bartender.

635
00:32:11.268 --> 00:32:13.390
I thought we were looking
for Ian Harmon.

636
00:32:13.556 --> 00:32:15.183
We were. This is the guy
that shot Ian Harmon.

637
00:32:15.349 --> 00:32:16.533
So why'd he call you?

638
00:32:16.658 --> 00:32:18.785
He wants us to turn Harmon
over in the next 24 hours.

639
00:32:18.910 --> 00:32:21.147
Or he's going
to kill more innocent people.

640
00:32:21.313 --> 00:32:22.274
Do we know where Harmon is?

641
00:32:22.440 --> 00:32:24.257
Not yet.

642
00:32:24.382 --> 00:32:26.152
We're not going to be held
hostage by some kind of lunatic.

643
00:32:26.318 --> 00:32:28.572
- Do we know anything about him?
- Not much.

644
00:32:28.738 --> 00:32:30.797
But I believe him.

645
00:32:30.922 --> 00:32:32.284
We ran his name.
but came up with nothing.

646
00:32:32.450 --> 00:32:35.235
Sir. got the I.D. Back on that phone.

647
00:32:35.360 --> 00:32:36.603
Bad news is it's a burner.

648
00:32:36.728 --> 00:32:37.831
Purchased and activated yesterday.

649
00:32:37.997 --> 00:32:39.806
- Any good news?
- Yes. sir.

650
00:32:39.931 --> 00:32:41.674
Phone was at this address downtown

651
00:32:41.799 --> 00:32:43.676
when we triangulated it
three minutes ago...

652
00:32:43.801 --> 00:32:45.130
Place called Reginald's cameras.

653
00:32:45.296 --> 00:32:49.272
Miss. your passport.

654
00:32:56.314 --> 00:32:57.657
Thank you so much.

655
00:32:57.782 --> 00:33:00.145
- What do I owe you?
- Nothing.

656
00:33:00.311 --> 00:33:03.356
- I-I'm sorry.
- For what?

657
00:33:03.522 --> 00:33:07.700
Your brother.
He was a good friend.

658
00:33:07.825 --> 00:33:13.006
Thank you.

659
00:33:22.890 --> 00:33:25.485
Well done.

660
00:33:25.610 --> 00:33:27.937
You promise you won't hurt my family?

661
00:33:28.062 --> 00:33:29.122
Of course not.

662
00:33:29.247 --> 00:33:30.456
You kept your end of the bargain.

663
00:33:30.581 --> 00:33:34.561
I would never dream
of touching your family.

664
00:33:38.390 --> 00:33:46.363
♪ ♪

665
00:34:27.189 --> 00:34:32.785
That must be the burner phone.

666
00:34:32.910 --> 00:34:35.912
He's playing us.

667
00:34:48.168 --> 00:34:50.338
Oh. hi. Are you open?

668
00:34:50.504 --> 00:34:51.571
I'm sorry. we're closed.

669
00:34:51.696 --> 00:34:52.739
Why don't you come back tomorrow?

670
00:34:52.864 --> 00:34:53.973
We open at 9:00.

671
00:34:54.098 --> 00:34:55.074
Oh. please. just a minute.

672
00:34:55.199 --> 00:34:57.210
I was told
I could get some help here.

673
00:34:57.335 --> 00:35:01.280
Give me a minute.
I'll see what I can do.

674
00:35:01.405 --> 00:35:05.353
Thank you.
Thank you so much.

675
00:35:25.129 --> 00:35:28.131
Where is he?

676
00:35:37.975 --> 00:35:43.016
Oh. it's a good likeness.
don't you think?

677
00:35:43.182 --> 00:35:46.526
Look. I'd prefer not
to hurt you. so go ahead.

678
00:35:46.651 --> 00:35:47.860
Call him.

679
00:35:47.985 --> 00:35:50.663
We'll see whose life
is more important to him.

680
00:35:50.788 --> 00:35:52.899
Go on.

681
00:35:57.238 --> 00:35:59.238
Hey. did you make it back from...

682
00:35:59.363 --> 00:36:01.034
He's here.
Get Ian to safety.

683
00:36:01.200 --> 00:36:03.843
Are you done?

684
00:36:03.968 --> 00:36:06.581
Have you said all you wanted to?

685
00:36:06.747 --> 00:36:08.648
May I?

686
00:36:08.773 --> 00:36:11.050
Thank you.

687
00:36:11.175 --> 00:36:12.935
Ian?

688
00:36:13.060 --> 00:36:15.455
I swear. if you touch
a hair on her head...

689
00:36:15.580 --> 00:36:16.756
I don't know who you are.

690
00:36:16.881 --> 00:36:18.191
but let me keep it simple for you.

691
00:36:18.316 --> 00:36:21.930
If you do not deliver
Ian Harmon to me in 15 minutes.

692
00:36:22.096 --> 00:36:24.015
I will kill your girlfriend.

693
00:36:38.279 --> 00:36:39.239
{pub}Yeah. Burkhardt.

694
00:36:39.405 --> 00:36:41.530
We have a problem.
We're going back to the shop.

695
00:36:41.655 --> 00:36:43.315
Waltz has Rosalee.

696
00:36:43.440 --> 00:36:45.161
He wants to make a trade.

697
00:36:45.411 --> 00:36:47.705
No. he's not gonna trade.
He's gonna kill you all.

698
00:36:48.122 --> 00:36:49.666
Well. if you got
a better plan. I'm all ears.

699
00:36:50.040 --> 00:36:52.257
Just. um. give me five minutes.

700
00:36:52.382 --> 00:36:53.461
Maybe I can come up with one.

701
00:36:53.627 --> 00:36:56.339
We don't have five minutes. Nick.

702
00:36:56.505 --> 00:36:58.591
Don't do anything until I get there.

703
00:36:58.757 --> 00:36:59.931
I'll wait as long as I can.

704
00:37:00.056 --> 00:37:04.002
but if push comes to shove.
I'm shoving.

705
00:37:04.127 --> 00:37:08.140
You may think I'm a monster. but...

706
00:37:08.265 --> 00:37:11.643
What I am is necessary.

707
00:37:11.768 --> 00:37:14.546
No society can survive without order.

708
00:37:14.671 --> 00:37:16.348
Free thought is not free.

709
00:37:16.473 --> 00:37:18.283
There's no such thing as revolution.

710
00:37:18.408 --> 00:37:20.986
The oppressed always become
the oppressors.

711
00:37:21.111 --> 00:37:24.159
And the cycle repeats itself
over and over.

712
00:37:24.325 --> 00:37:29.728
The only way to win is
to stay out of the cycle.

713
00:37:29.853 --> 00:37:33.131
You don't understand a word
that I've been saying.

714
00:37:33.256 --> 00:37:38.756
I'm sorry. I wasn't listening.

715
00:37:38.922 --> 00:37:40.806
No. no.
You're staying here.

716
00:37:40.931 --> 00:37:42.474
No. no. no.
This is my fight.

717
00:37:42.599 --> 00:37:43.759
Nobody's gonna fight it for me.

718
00:37:43.884 --> 00:37:44.926
The second he sees you. you're dead.

719
00:37:45.051 --> 00:37:46.228
He doesn't know who I am.

720
00:37:46.353 --> 00:37:47.429
That doesn't mean
he's not gonna kill you.

721
00:37:47.554 --> 00:37:48.975
Yeah. I get that.

722
00:37:49.141 --> 00:37:52.417
But we're not doing anything
until we find out about Rosalee.

723
00:37:52.542 --> 00:37:53.885
If she isn't already dead.

724
00:37:54.010 --> 00:37:56.191
Don't let your emotions
get the better of you.

725
00:37:56.357 --> 00:37:57.923
He <i>will</i> use that to his advantage.

726
00:37:58.048 --> 00:38:00.783
That's why he took her.

727
00:38:03.854 --> 00:38:05.564
I have a plan.

728
00:38:05.689 --> 00:38:06.865
You do? For real?

729
00:38:06.990 --> 00:38:09.134
Yeah. I'm going in.
you're staying out.

730
00:38:09.259 --> 00:38:11.036
No. no. no.
You don't understand waltz.

731
00:38:11.161 --> 00:38:12.457
I understand him
better than you think I do.

732
00:38:12.623 --> 00:38:13.708
He won't be expecting me

733
00:38:13.874 --> 00:38:15.474
and he doesn't know my
connection to any of you.

734
00:38:15.599 --> 00:38:19.130
- So what does that get us?
- Time.

735
00:38:23.807 --> 00:38:28.723
Well. it seems like
your Fuchsbau hero is a coward.

736
00:38:28.889 --> 00:38:31.351
Waltz.

737
00:38:31.517 --> 00:38:32.602
- How did you know?
- You want Ian?

738
00:38:32.768 --> 00:38:34.521
- I've got him.
- What?

739
00:38:35.151 --> 00:38:36.314
Shut up.
Get on the floor.

740
00:38:36.480 --> 00:38:38.691
Get on the floor.

741
00:38:38.857 --> 00:38:41.194
If you've got him. where is he?

742
00:38:44.405 --> 00:38:46.115
- Whoa!
- Who are you?

743
00:38:46.949 --> 00:38:48.335
I'm the guy you called.
I've got Ian.

744
00:38:48.460 --> 00:38:49.160
Who's he?

745
00:38:49.326 --> 00:38:50.995
What the hell is going on here?

746
00:38:51.161 --> 00:38:52.010
You're gonna believe a Fuchsbau?

747
00:38:52.135 --> 00:38:54.079
What are you trying to say. buddy?

748
00:38:54.204 --> 00:38:56.292
- I'm saying you're a liar.
- All Fuchsbaus are liars.

749
00:38:56.458 --> 00:38:57.669
Who did you call?

750
00:38:57.835 --> 00:38:59.212
I didn't call a Fuchsbau.

751
00:38:59.378 --> 00:39:04.217
It's true.
I'm not a Fuchsbau.

752
00:39:05.931 --> 00:39:06.928
Blutbad.

753
00:39:17.229 --> 00:39:19.941
Are you okay?

754
00:39:20.107 --> 00:39:23.945
- It's over.
- No. it's not.

755
00:39:28.271 --> 00:39:31.049
Hey.
Put the gun down.

756
00:39:31.174 --> 00:39:33.246
I can't.
He's right.

757
00:39:33.412 --> 00:39:36.288
Even if he's dead.
they'll send others after me.

758
00:39:36.413 --> 00:39:37.709
Ian.

759
00:39:37.875 --> 00:39:38.876
Oh!

760
00:39:45.549 --> 00:39:49.024
But at least now your friends
will be safe.

761
00:39:52.228 --> 00:39:55.474
Sometimes it's hard to know
that the right thing is.

762
00:39:55.599 --> 00:39:59.355
Sometimes it's not.

763
00:40:07.827 --> 00:40:08.823
Nick.

764
00:40:08.989 --> 00:40:10.155
Nick. please.

765
00:40:10.280 --> 00:40:11.576
If the Verrat knows where Ian is...

766
00:40:11.742 --> 00:40:17.373
You've got other things
to worry about.

767
00:40:17.539 --> 00:40:18.597
I'm so sorry.

768
00:40:18.722 --> 00:40:22.420
Don't be.

769
00:40:31.635 --> 00:40:33.512
Nick. come on. you can't do this.

770
00:40:33.637 --> 00:40:36.017
- He killed waltz to protect us.
- Listen to me.

771
00:40:36.183 --> 00:40:39.017
There's only one thing
that you need to do.

772
00:40:39.142 --> 00:40:40.229
What?

773
00:40:40.395 --> 00:40:44.689
Get rid of waltz's body.

774
00:40:44.814 --> 00:40:47.816
Yeah. Okay.

775
00:40:52.950 --> 00:40:53.898
Come on.

776
00:41:11.841 --> 00:41:15.390
Get out.

777
00:41:15.556 --> 00:41:18.309
What are you doing?

778
00:41:18.475 --> 00:41:20.925
I'm saving my friends.

779
00:41:21.050 --> 00:41:24.273
If you go to trial. they'll be dead.

780
00:41:30.195 --> 00:41:31.864
Don't come back.

781
00:42:08.031 --> 00:42:11.237
How do you know this is waltz?

782
00:42:11.403 --> 00:42:13.489
Passport.
Found it in his pocket.

783
00:42:13.655 --> 00:42:15.783
And the Luger.
we believe it's the gun used

784
00:42:15.949 --> 00:42:17.618
to shoot the bartender
and the camera store owner.

785
00:42:17.784 --> 00:42:18.750
What about Ian Harmon?

786
00:42:18.875 --> 00:42:20.329
We think he did this?

787
00:42:20.495 --> 00:42:23.221
If someone was trying to kill me.

788
00:42:23.346 --> 00:42:25.126
I'd be trying to kill them.

789
00:42:25.548 --> 00:42:27.837
We ever catch up with this
guy. maybe we'll find out.

790
00:42:28.003 --> 00:42:29.844
I wouldn't be so sure.

791
00:42:29.969 --> 00:42:32.091
Some one else may catch up
with him first.

792
00:42:32.341 --> 00:42:34.927
This world is on the brink of war.

793
00:42:35.218 --> 00:42:38.681
